\dfrac{\partial V(t,x)}{\partial t}+h(x)=0
\dfrac{\partial V(t,x)}{\partial t}=-h(x)
V(t,x)=C(x)-h(x)t
V(T,x)=\Phi(x)
C(x)-h(x)T=\Phi(x)
C(x)=\Phi(x)+h(x)T
\therefore V(t,x)=\Phi(x)+h(x)T-h(x)t=\Phi(x)+h(x)(T-t)
